The paper deals with machine learning models for online advertising, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze user behavior and advertiser content. The proposed models also use ensemble techniques and specialized data sampling methodologies, which are common in machine learning (LG) and computational engineering (CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of variations in product demand, which could be related to data science (DS) and computational economics (CE). Finally, the paper focuses on predicting user interactions with product-related advertisements, which could be relevant to computational linguistics (CL).
